{
  "texts": [
    "One possible implementation of this approach is to take g (θ) enkf,t (x t |y 0:t, x1:N t) as the density associated with an ensemble member generated by the update step of Algorithm 3, for a suitable choice of H and R, and conditional on the forecast ensemble x1:N t.",
    "The weight function then takes the form wt (x 1:N t, x",
    "However, in many scenarios of practical interest, it is beneficial to model states at a finer frequency than at which observations are observed.",
    "In this case, the state vector x t is replaced by the matrix (x t,1,.",
    ", x t,m), whose elements can be simulated recursively from some kernel p (θ)"
  ]
}